usdPppoeAgent.name: usdPppoeAgent

revisions.description: Added AC-NAME and duplicate MAC address indicator objects.
The initial release of this management information module.

usdPppoeAgent.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPppoeAgent.description: The agent capabilities definitions for the point-to-point protocol over Ethernet (PPPoE) component of the SNMP agent in the Unisphere Data Routing Switch family of products.

usdPppoeAgentV1.name: usdPppoeAgentV1
usdPppoeAgentV1.productrelease:
Version 1 of the PPPoE component of the Unisphere Routing Switch SNMP
        agent.  This version of the PPPoE component was supported in the
        Unisphere RX 3.0 thru 3.2.2 system releases.
usdPppoeAgentV1.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in the Unisphere Routing Switch. These capabilities became obsolete when AC-NAME and duplicate MAC address indicator objects were added.

usdPppoeAgentV2.name: usdPppoeAgentV2
usdPppoeAgentV2.productrelease:
Version 2 of the PPPoE component of the Unisphere Routing Switch SNMP
        agent.  This version of the PPPoE component was supported in the
        Unisphere RX 3.2.3 through 3.x system releases.
usdPppoeAgentV2.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in the Unisphere Routing Switch. These capabilities became obsolete when PADI flag support was added.

usdPppoeAgentV3.name: usdPppoeAgentV3
usdPppoeAgentV3.productrelease:
Version 3 of the PPPoE component of the Unisphere Routing Switch SNMP
        agent.  This version of the PPPoE component is supported in the
        Unisphere RX 4.0 and subsequent system releases.
usdPppoeAgentV3.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the PPPoE application in the Unisphere Routing Switch.
